
Organizational Development Report - KCB
Organizational Development (OD) Report
Organization Overview:
Kenya Commercial Bank (KCB) is one of the largest financial institutions in East Africa. It operates in the
banking sector with a network of over 200 branches and thousands of employees. KCB provides retail,
corporate, and investment banking services. As an Organizational Development (OD) Consultant, I was
tasked with assessing the internal leadership and team dynamics to address performance challenges.
PART A: Leadership and Team Dynamics (7 Marks)
1. Leadership Styles (3 Marks):
The prevailing leadership style in KCB is largely transactional at the operational level, characterized by
structured roles and reward-based performance systems. However, top management demonstrates
transformational traits through strategic vision and innovation initiatives. For example, branch managers often
focus on targets and KPIs, rewarding high performance without engaging deeply with staff development.
Recommendation: Introduce more transformational leadership at middle levels to encourage innovation and
employee engagement. This can involve leadership coaching, delegation, and inclusive decision-making.
2. Emotional Intelligence and Team Development (2 Marks):
The level of emotional intelligence varies across departments. In high-performing teams, leaders exhibit
strong empathy, active listening, and emotional regulation, which positively impacts communication and
collaboration.
However, some teams experience interpersonal friction due to poor self-awareness and lack of empathy in
supervisors. This has affected team morale and trust.
Recommendation: Implement emotional intelligence training as part of leadership development to boost team
cohesion and performance.
