3. Conflict Resolution Strategy (2 Marks):
A recurring conflict involves inter-departmental blame during system downtimes, causing friction between IT
and customer service teams. This delays problem resolution and lowers customer satisfaction.
Recommended OD-based strategy: Facilitate cross-functional mediation and implement structured conflict
resolution frameworks. Regular feedback sessions and team-building activities can also foster mutual
understanding.
PART B: Diagnosis and Problem Solving in OD (8 Marks)
1. Diagnostic Tools (SWOT Analysis)
Strengths Strong brand presence
Strengths Broad customer base
Strengths Diverse financial services
Weaknesses Bureaucratic decision-making
Weaknesses Low employee engagement in some units
Weaknesses Resistance to digital transformation
Opportunities Growing fintech partnerships
Opportunities Government projects and initiatives
Threats Increasing competition from digital banks
Threats Regulatory changes and cyber threats
Insights:
- KCB has a strong market position but struggles internally with team cohesion and resistance to change.
- Employee feedback highlighted frustration with delayed decision-making and poor communication in
mid-level teams.
